headline: Phillips 66 Partners With NextEra to Build Solar Facility Near Rodeo Plant -- OPIS
summary: Phillips 66 said Tuesday it is partnering with the largest U.S. electric utility NextEra to build a 30.2 MW solar facility to power its Rodeo renewable fuel production plant in northern California. ...

headline: Phillips 66 teams with NextEra Energy Resources to power Rodeo Renewable Energy Complex with solar facility
summary: HOUSTON, December 10, 2024--Phillips 66 is teaming up with a subsidiary of NextEra Energy Resources, LLC to power Phillips 66’s Rodeo Renewable Energy Complex.
